  "texts": [
    "Based on participants' rationales and conversation intentions behind their customized chatbots, we further categorized these chatbot personas into five groups (see Table 3): participants did not only seek emotional reliance by customizing the chatbot to play their beloved pets and close friends but also confronted stressors that caused pain or trouble to them.",
    "Moreover, they engaged in intellectual discourse by speaking to philosophical and scientific figures, with whom they explored the meanings of life.",
    "Additionally, they customized the chatbot to play a mirror of themselves to foster self-discovery.",
    "Last but not least, as expected, they requested therapeutic support from virtual domain experts or psychologists.Overall, participants recognized that customizing chatbots allowed them to \"construct\" various characters tailored to different contexts of emotional struggles.",
    "For example, when facing academic pressure, P4 customized the chatbot to act as their PhD supervisor to better understand their supervisor's expectations and navigate academic challenges; when feeling lonely, the participant made the chatbot a cute little daughter, with whom they played the role of a mother to engage in affectionate interactions that brightened their mood and provided comfort."
  ],
